= Day 1: Brainstorm problems

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
List 10 things that annoy you or people around you. Think about daily frustrations, wasted time, or small expenses.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
It's harder than it looks to find truly painful problems. You might only get 3-4 good ones.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have at least 5 distinct problems written down.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 2: Pick your top 3 problems

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
From your list, choose the 3 problems you understand best and feel most strongly about solving.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
You might be tempted to pick the 'coolest' problem, but stick to the one you know intimately.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have 3 specific problems identified as your focus.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 3: Who has this problem?

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
For each of your top 3 problems, list 5 types of people or groups who likely experience it. Be specific.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
It's easy to be vague. Push yourself to name actual job titles or demographics.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You can clearly describe the likely customer for each problem.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 4: Your first victim (interview)

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Reach out to 1 person (friend, family, acquaintance) and ask about one of your problems using Script 1. Just listen.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
They might give short answers. It will feel a bit awkward.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You've had one conversation about a real problem.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 5: Interview 2 & 3

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Talk to 2 more people about a problem. Try using Script 2 to dig deeper into their pain.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
One might be super helpful, the other might just nod along. That's normal.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You've completed 3 problem-focused conversations.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 6: Summarize problem feedback

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Review your interview notes. Write down 3 key insights or common frustrations you heard about your chosen problem.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
The insights might not be groundbreaking, but any pattern is useful.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have written summaries of what people said about their problems.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 7: Brainstorm tiny solutions

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
For your strongest problem, list 5 ways you could offer a super small, simple solution. Think 'minimum viable offer'.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
Your ideas might still be too grand. Try to make them even smaller.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have 5 potential tiny offers listed.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 8: Pick your tiniest offer

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Choose the one tiny offer from your list that requires almost no work or resources to deliver. Make it ridiculously simple.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
It should feel a bit silly because it's so small. If it feels like a lot of work, it's not tiny enough.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have a one-sentence description of your smallest possible offer.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 9: Who to pitch?

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
List 5 people you could approach about your tiny offer. Try to go beyond just friends and family.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
Finding non-friends is hard. Think about online communities, professional networks.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have 5 target contacts or groups for your pitch.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 10: First tiny offer pitch

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Using Script 3 or 4, contact 1 person with your tiny offer. Be direct.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
They might not reply. You might feel nervous or awkward. This is normal.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You've made your first direct pitch.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 11: Second pitch

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Contact another person with your tiny offer. Don't wait for a reply from the first one.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
Still low replies is a common result. Don't take it personally.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You've made two pitches.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 12: Third pitch

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Contact a third person with your tiny offer. Keep it consistent.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
The process still feels repetitive, but you're gathering data.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You've made three pitches.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 13: Review pitches so far

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Look at your 3 pitches. How many replies? Any 'yes' or 'no' responses? Any signs of interest?
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
You might have zero positive replies. This is a very valuable data point.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
You have honest notes on the reception of your first pitches.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 14: Refine your tiny offer

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Based on any feedback (or lack of it), tweak your tiny offer or how you describe it to make it clearer or more appealing.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Reality]
#v(3pt)
It's hard to refine without much data. Make your best educated guess.
]

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Win condition]
#v(3pt)
Your tiny offer description is slightly changed or improved.
]

#pagebreak()
= Day 15: Identify 5 more contacts

#block(inset: 8pt, radius: 4pt, stroke: 0.5pt, fill: rgb("FFFFFF"))[#strong[Action]
#v(3pt)
Find 5 new people or groups who might benefit from your refined tiny offer.
